      "message": "I have updated a new version. We don\u0027t need to check `mBackendDevice` is null or not multiple times in order to use the mutex anymore. We can query the mutex from the device in ctor and keep a ref of the mutex. If the device doesn\u0027t have mutex (due to ImplicitDeviceSynchronization disabled), this will just store a nullptr ref.\n\nLater we can use `Autolock` directly on the mutex\u0027s ref. `AutoLock` on a null mutex is no-op. Even after `mBackendDevice` is set to null in `Destroy`, the mutex\u0027s ref will still be valid to be locked.\n\nPTAL @enga@chromium.org @cwallez@chromium.org @sunnyps@chromium.org",
